Common.Highlight.Common.Text: The largest contiguous block of vacant space in Western PA - over 540,000 RSF available
New lobby and two-story glass façade
Largest back-up generator capacity in Western PA: four generators with total capacity of 3,750 kW to sustain all building functions
Redundant fiber optic service entering building at different points
Adjacent to Mellon Square Park – $12 million renovation completed in 2015 580 parking spaces
Immediately adjacent to Light Rail “T” station
Directly located on new Bus Rapid Transit line to Oakland
Fifth Avenue, William Penn Place, and Smithfield Street all have on-street bike routes

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: An iconic Pittsburgh high-rise has been transformed into a modern space with market leading amenities. This 915,956 RSF, 41-story building is Energy Star Rated, and has over 540,000 RSF of office space available.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Redefine Your Corporate Culture at the All-New 525 William Penn Place
